history.content: That schedule is manageable. Keep in mind EE 16A is designed for freshmen, so as long as you keep up with lecture you will be fine. I would say 160 depends on your group, so look into finding people you can trust to carry their weight.

That schedule is manageable. Keep in mind EE 16A is designed for freshmen, so as long as you keep up with lecture you will be fine. 168 is one of the lighter workload upper division courses with 1 midterm, 1 final, and 3 projects/hw [average of 20 hrs]. I would say 160 depends on your group, so look into finding people you can trust to carry their weight.

Graduating senior here who need to take EE16A and two other upper div classes to graduate (in Fall 2018).

How heavy is this workload? To give a perspective, CS 170 + 161 + 186 turned out to be not manageable for me given my other commitments.

I am currently enrolled in 16A and 160, but I have heard that the workload for 160 could vary, and I would like to get opinions on that (Paulos is teaching 160 in the fall).

Since I have not taken Data 8, I have decided to drop DS100 in favor for 186, which I can enroll without issue. Since the website for DS100 said they will expand the class, it phase 2 DS100 feasible?
